A method reference is the shorthand syntax for a lambda expression that contains just one method call.

class Main {

    static void print(String s) {
        System.out.println(s);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        List<String> names = new ArrayList<>();
        names.add("Mohammed");
        names.add("Ahmed");
        names.add("Khan");

        names.stream().forEach(Main::print);  // âœ… Valid method reference to instance method
        name.forEach(System.out::println);
    }
}

Used for iterating over collections and stream operations.